I come across the similar issues, too. And I suggest that you may check the import file in the file tree D:\Program Files\Anaconda3\lib\site-packages\tensorflow\contrib\tensor_forest\python\ops_training_ops
I think it may be caused by version of tensorflow. And in the ReadMe.md file of contrib, you can read that "Any code in this directory is not officially supported, and may change or be removed at any time without notice". So in different versions, the files in contrib may change. Pls take care of this

body:
I come across the similar issues, too. And I suggest that you may check the import file in the file tree `D:\Program Files\Anaconda3\lib\site-packages\tensorflow\contrib\tensor_forest\python\ops_training_ops`
I think it may be caused by version of tensorflow. And in the ReadMe.md file of contrib, you can read that "Any code in this directory is not officially supported, and may change or be removed at any time without notice". So in different versions, the files in contrib may change. Pls take care of this
